OL,7,FNadia*, a Sudanese secondary school
OL,8,Fteacher, begins to cry. She is
OL,9,Fsitting in a makeshift tent in one of
OL,10,FSouth Sudan's refugee camps, which
OL,11,Fhouses around 10,000 people who have
OL,12,Ffled bloody violence north of the
OL,13,Fborder.
OL,15,FThe sun beats down through the brown
OL,16,Fand orange fabrics which have been
OL,17,Fhooked onto sticks to create a
OL,18,Fshelter for her and her five children.
OL,3,C'I had to leave my mother behind':
OL,4,CFleeing civilians reveal chilling
OL,5,Cdetails of life in Sudan
